This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing. It may also belong to "Sound" (cs.SD) as it deals with audio data. "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) is another likely category as the paper discusses using pre-trained models for feature extraction. "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) are also possible categories as the paper discusses developing speech recognizers for low resource languages and adapting to different domains, which are relevant topics in these fields.
